    {
      "id": "note-security",
      "title": "Password Security Checklist",
      "content": "### Password Security Checklist\n\n- [x] Use unique passwords for each service\n- [x] Use a password manager (SecureVault!)\n- [ ] Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) everywhere possible\n- [ ] Change critical passwords every 6-12 months\n- [ ] Avoid public Wi-Fi for sensitive transactions\n- [ ] Regular security audits\n- [ ] Monitor for data breaches\n\n### Best Practices\n- Minimum 12 characters\n- Mix of letters, numbers, symbols\n- No personal information\n- Different password for each account",
      "notebook": "Security",
      "tags": [
        "security",
        "checklist",
        "passwords",
        "2fa"
      ],
      "isPinned": true,
      "noteType": "rich",
      "createdAt": "2024-01-15T00:00:00.000Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-01-15T00:00:00.000Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "note-budget",
      "title": "Monthly Budget Template",
      "content": "## Monthly Budget - March 2024\n\n### Income\n- Salary: $7,500\n- Freelance: $800\n- Investment Returns: $200\n- **Total Income: $8,500**\n\n### Fixed Expenses\n- Rent: $2,000\n- Utilities: $200\n- Insurance: $150\n- **Total Fixed: $2,350**\n\n### Variable Expenses\n- Groceries: $600\n- Transportation: $400\n- Subscriptions: $120\n- Entertainment: $300\n- **Total Variable: $1,420**\n\n### Savings Goals\n- Emergency Fund: $1,000\n- Retirement: $2,000\n- House Fund: $1,500\n- Vacation Fund: $500\n- **Total Savings: $5,000**\n\n### Summary\n- Total Expenses: $3,770\n- Total Savings: $5,000\n- **Remaining: -$270**\n\n*Need to reduce variable expenses by $270*",
      "notebook": "Finance",
      "tags": [
        "budget",
